EN:
This project is distributed under GPL-3.0-or-later.

The project was originally inspired by ESPHome wireless M-Bus component work
from SzczepanLeon/esphome-components and by related wmbusmeters code paths.
The current repository has diverged into an independent RAW-only RF->MQTT
bridge architecture:

- no meter decoding on the ESP device,
- no Home Assistant sensor/entity creation on the ESP device,
- validated Wireless M-Bus telegram forwarding to MQTT,
- external decoding by wmbusmeters / Home Assistant / Linux,
- extended RF diagnostics and receive-path counters,
- SX1262/SX1276-focused receive paths and long-packet handling.

Some source files may retain structural, naming, or code-level ancestry from
that ecosystem. Those files are marked with SPDX headers and are distributed
under GPL-3.0-or-later.

